Temasek Holdingsâ€™ stock bets shrank by the most in more than 17 years after taking some cash off the table and incurring steep paper losses on BlackRock  Amazon  PayPal and Airbnb. It retained most of its stakes in Alibaba Group Holding and other Chinese stocks.2. The Singapore state investment firm held 97 stocks valued at US$18.33 billion on June 30  according to its 13F regulatory filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission late on Monday. It listed 96 stocks worth US$23.97 billion on March 31.3.
